ape, showing the natural heritage that has enabled the agricultural success of the region today. The innovative research of Grossinger and his historical ecology team allows us to visualize the past in unprecedented detail, improving our understanding of the living landscapes we inhabit and suggesting strategies to increase their health and resilience in the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEcologyzCaliforniazNapa ValleyxHistoryvMaps. 0aLandscape changeszCaliforniazNapa ValleyvMaps. 0aLandscapeszCaliforniazNapa ValleyxHistoryvMaps. 0aNatural historyzCaliforniazNapa ValleyvMaps. 0aPhysical geographyzCaliforniazNapa ValleyxHistoryvMaps. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  aamerican ecology.  aamerican history.  aamerican maps.  abooks for californians.  acalifornia agriculture.  acalifornia and wine.  acalifornia environment.  acalifornia historical maps.  acalifornia history.  acalifornia landscape.  acalifornia travel.  acalifornia wetlands.  acalifornia wildflowers.  aenvironment conservation.  aenvironment protection.  aexploring california.  agoing green.  agreat american outdoors.  ahistorical ecology.  ahistory of napa valley.  alandscapes.  anorcal books.  awest coast ecology.  awest coast landscape.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026910140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095172340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951723423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951723/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY